==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diabase
<hw>Di"a*base</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>diabase</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>dia`basis</grk> a crossing or passing
over, fr. <grk>dia`</grk> + <grk>bai`nw</grk> to go; -- so called by
<person>Brongniart</person>, because it passes over to diorite.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A basic, dark-colored, holocrystalline, igneous
rock, consisting essentially of a triclinic feldspar and pyroxene with
magnetic iron; -- often limited to rocks pretertiary in age. It includes
part of what was early called <partof>greenstone</partof>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diabaterial</ent>⟦br⟧
